=== 10 ML MODELS (5-layer pipeline) ===
Layer 1 (Safety, always first): Crisis Detector — RoBERTa + 30+ keywords, 7-class, 5000 examples, <100ms
Layer 2 (Signal, parallel): Emotion (DistilBERT 8-class 8000ex) + Intent (DistilBERT 7-class 4000ex) + Sentiment (DistilBERT 3-class 2000ex)
Layer 3 (Domain): Topic (DistilBERT multi-label 5-class 2000ex) + Booking Intent (DistilBERT binary+NER 1000ex) + Assessment Router (RoBERTa 9-class 4000ex)
Layer 4 (NLP, Stage 2 only): Meta-Model Detector — AllenNLP SRL + Flan-T5-large LoRA (detects cognitive distortions)
Layer 5 (Generation): LoRA Stage 1 (Qwen r=8 634ex) + LoRA Stage 2 (Qwen r=16 3017ex)
All classifier outputs injected into LLM system prompt.

=== AI PIPELINE (process_message) ===
1. Load session (Redis cache → DB fallback)
2. Crisis scan (ALWAYS, NEVER SKIP) — if crisis: escalate (WebSocket + email)
3. asyncio.gather: emotion + intent + topic classifiers (parallel, 30ms each)
4. Build context blocks from classifier outputs
5. RAG query: Pinecone top-5 chunks for tenant namespace
6. Build system prompt (step, emotion, intent, topic, RAG context)
7. LLM inference: llama-cpp-python > Together AI > llama.cpp HTTP
8. Persist ChatMessages to DB (user + assistant)
9. Advance current_step++
10. Return response via WebSocket

=== LLM INFERENCE ROUTING (qwen_inference.py) ===
Priority: LLAMA_CPP_PYTHON_MODEL_PATH set → native in-process (fastest) 
> TOGETHER_API_KEY set → Together AI API (dev)
> else → llama.cpp HTTP server at LLAMA_CPP_SERVER_URL

